QID3: Event 1 was lockdown. It began with us walking through a school bus, through a yard, and then into a building. We walked up some steps and walked across flooring tiles that moved to throw us off balance. This part took roughly like 5 minutes to walk through.
QID6: The second event was the machine shop. This took place all inside. When we first walked in, we were treated to a giant rotating saw thrown in our faces as well as various taser like electrical devices on the wall. People were wandering around holding various tools.
QID7: The 3rd event was the blood yard. This was mostly outdoors and was supposed to be this overgrown, demonic garden type thing. Lot of voodoo stuff and strange looking plants and animals. I remember passing a chef who was cooking body parts. The last bit of this section took place in a building.
QID8: Event 4 was the infirmary. For this part, we all had to hold on to a piece of gauze and walk single  file through it. This event was populated with various nurses and mental patients. They asked for copious amount of my blood as a donation. I remember walking down a long hallway, with patients pulling on the bars of their cells and a doctor at the end of it operating on  a patient who appeared to be dead.
QID10: Event 5 was the quarantine 4D event. This was when I was first in line. We were all required to put 3D glasses on and the walls and props were painted with glow paint. The combination of the paint and the glasses created a very disorienting atmosphere. I saw a woman laughing in the corner and turned around the greet someone who had been trying to sneak up on me. At one point, we walked across a rope bridge. Then towards the end we walked across another bridge through a rotating cylinder, which threw me off balance for a second. At the end, we were asked to dispose of our glasses.
QID9: The final event of the night was the breakout. This section of the event was in almost complete darkness and I was the second person in line. I remember that, due to the darkness, the person leading our group was confused on which direction to proceed. At one point, we were required to move through these inflatable wall things that pancaked us in the middle. There was a second part of the inflatable walls that only covered our legs. After we finished this, the study ended.

QID3: while in line, waiting for the event to begin there was one group of girls who seemed very eager yet pretty spooked. As the line continued to grow an actor came out in front of the crowd with a glowing box. They held out the box towards the crowd when suddenly a fake head sprung from inside the box. The girls in front of the line shrieked.
QID6: Before our group entered I found out I would be the first one to lead the group through the first phase. I was slightly reluctant but excited to see how it would go
QID7: Upon entering for the first time, and turning the first corner of the first phase I was very startled by what I saw- an actor shackled to chains, suspended in air and thrashing violently. It was very jarring
QID8: While leading the first phase, there was one room in which there was heavy fog. This made in very difficult to see. I was shuffling slowly trying to make my way through the room. There were also "bodies" swaying from the ceiling. I found this room to be actually scary and was happy to get through it.
QID10: At the end of the first phase, the path led to an open room with more heavy fog. This room also had lasers pointing in multiple directions and people in robes that seemingly glided across the room. I thought this was quite disorienting.
QID9: After my turn to lead was over I went to the back of the line where my friend Collin was previously standing. He mentioned he did not like the back of the line because of the actors startling you from behind. I instantly did not want to be in the back of the line.
QID11: There was a moment in the blood yard when an actor revved up a chainsaw and scared me from behind. They continued to pursue me. The low visibility from the fog and the actor coming in and out my visibility with haste made it seems very real and very frightening
QID12: In the first phase that I was leading I was trailing behind another group. One girl from that group almost refused to enter the bus where we being led into as "prisoners". I laughed.
QID14: During the last phase my friend Collin seemed to struggle to get through one corridor as it was very dark and was made up of quishy walls that pressed into your sides, forcing one to feel their way through. He mentioned that he probably would not have made it through without the help of the group
QID15: It was difficult for me to put on the glasses provided at the entrance of the "quarantine 4D" phase because of my actual eye glasses. They would just fall off my face. I was a little frustrated because I wanted to have the full effect of the experience.
QID53: i would try to focus on getting through the room/ obstacle as quickly as possible
QID398: i thought about looking forward to how fun the experience would be
QID458: I tried hard to focus on where I was going, as i could not see well and not bump into any of the hanging bodies
QID488: while momentarily feeling a bit dizzy, I took a deep breath and focused on my steps. luckily by that time it was the end of the phase and we re grouped.
QID518: reminded myself the entire event is for fun and to enjoy
QID548: i picked up my pace so I could  get away from chainsaw lady
QID638: I tried my best on getting the glasses to stay on my face. towards the end it worked and it was the quarantine 4d phase was really cool to experience

QID3: Waiting in line for the Haunted House to open up. People were walking around and through the line dressed up as we were waiting.
QID6: Walking through the school bus with our group. I remember this distinctly as it was one of the first things we walked through and I was expected people to be hiding in the bus waiting to scare us but there was nobody.
QID7: Giving our first ranking on a scale of 1-5 how scary the first section of the haunted house was. I remember it being in a big open room with actors still walking around.

QID10: As we were walking through one of the stages of the haunted house, one of the actors got really close to me and tried to like breath/ scare me in my ear. I just remember him accidentally spitting on me a little.
QID9: The 3-D part of the trip was wild and stood out to me. I remember putting on the glasses and reaching for the wall so I could get a sense of how distorted my vision was. I remember one of the female actors telling me not to touch the wall cause it might touch back

QID15: I remember our leader mentioning to us that there was Al Capone's old speak easy in the prison still and you could visit/ tour it during the day. Me and my buddy already talked about going back.

QID3: First thing I remember is the plague doctor, which was at the very beginning and before any formal event even start. It was intriguing rather than scary, except the girls behind me yelled at it made me jolt and run into the next room.
QID6: Getting ready to walk onto the school bus, I felt very anxious. This was another event that was before any formal event. There were bodies on the bus and I also remember trying to hurry out of there
QID7: Before entering the first event, where the prisoners were breaking out, there was a guard who was zombified at the control panel and was telling us to turn around and leave. There was an immediate sense to leave, however we were ushered into the next room.
QID8: There was a butcher shop/meat room, where there were hanging white bags. This was absolutely the most terrifying moment, as these types of rooms have always made me fearful. I remember a man in a pig mask and looking at all the swinging white bags scared if something would pop out. Looked at the floor after staring at a jump scare and rushed out.
QID10: Upon entering the hospital setting, I recall feeling underwelmed, yet getting ready to be scared. The hallway was spacious and there were nurses and doctors with a gurney and a patient on it. They were shaking the patient saying something was wrong. I also remember thinking back to when I took a day tour of the prison and felt somewhat calm knowing where I was. However, we were then ushered into the more crowded event.
QID9: During the hospital, there was a room with a dentist chair. This stuck out to me since the whole hospital was just gory and had a lot of fake body parts scattered. Since I hate the dentist, I can remember him asking us (holding pliers) if we were next. It was a brief event out of the hospital, and was not filled with jump scares, before we went into the next room.
QID11: In the 4D quarantine, I was completely entertained and felt distracted by all the visuals. There was a tunnel that spun and felt like you were "in space". There was also a room that looked like there was a bunch of glow paint and a ball pit. There were also clowns, which were not personally terrifying.
QID12: In 4D quarantine we had to walk through these air filled squishy things. It was short lived but extremely odd and put me out of place. There was a brief scare but I was too distracted by the feeling of being squished to react.
QID14: Knowing it was the last event, we walked into complete darkness. So dark that actors that jumped out weren't scary as it was hard to see. QID15: The last event was hard to process, as it was extremely over stimulating. QID3: The first 'scary' environment was the bus right at the beginning of the first section. After entering Eastern State and filling in consent forms, just past the section where they ask if you want blood painted on your face, you are held for a moment and then allowed through. At this point, you board a bus, dimly lit, with several people sitting in seats throughout. There is a near-constant strobe, so it is difficult to make out objects, but I kept waiting for someone to jump out from behind a seat the whole way through - this did not happen. Upon reflection, this was most likely just to build anticipation, but it was super scary regardless.
QID6: After the bus, there was a kind of mock jail with some cells containing animatronic figures - some hanging from chains, some not - and prisoners/guards all over moving us through the place. This was one of the most uncomfortable sections, because guards were seeking to jump scare anyone they could, and it was consistently very dark or strobe-lit, so motion and objects were inconsistent and hard to pick out.
QID7: In the very last section, there were a couple of ballon-typed tunnels that touched us. You could tell they were just full of air, but they were the only things through the whole event with which we interacted physically, which made that experience the worst of any. I think the biggest problem was the inevitability of it touching me. I didn't want to touch anything, but you couldn't get away from it.
QID8: In the fifth and sixth sections, one of the other participants requested that I walk at the tail of the group so that she wasn't stuck back there. It's easy to tell that the actors often seek to jump-scare the first and last person in a group the size of ours. I agreed, because I didn't want her to be extra frightened the whole time. She was right. It was worse. The actors can sneak up behind you and spend more time yelling or surprise you a second time. It's not cool.
QID10: Overall, the excess loud noise was the worst feature for me. I am a musician and sound engineer, and while I'm not any more sensitive to sounds than anyone else, I do tend to unintentionally pay more attention to sound. The jump scares were often accompanied by properly loud screams and cracks - probably between 90-100dB.
QID9: Again throughout, there were regular blasts of pressurized air around our heads and feet. Clearly, this is just to disorient and prime us for jump scares to come. Still, the anticipation of not knowing when one will hit you was uncomfortable, and the extended stress of it was disconcerting. These air blasts were also extremely loud.
QID11: When I was leading in the second section, we were supposed to be ducking under/around some lasers in the big hallway, and being yelled at if we did not do so. At one point, I was staring down the hall to try and make out some consistent movement to focus on as I was walking. In the midst of the strobe lights, there were suddenly several black-clad people just wafting past me getting very close. It was pretty scary, because they appeared and disappeared in a matter of moments.
QID12: The actors in the machine shop were especially scary. Even though they couldn't touch us, they were all doing various things, usually to body parts, that gave you just enough information to be terrified at the possibilities.
QID14: I didn't like that in each line waiting for each new section, there were yet more actors waiting to frighten you. It seemed like they were all just waiting for eye contact, so I made a practice of not looking at any of them.
QID15: There was one particular actor/moment that I found disturbing. In the hallway entering the infirmary, there was a person standing next to a gurney with this animatronic character that was retching and screaming. The actor was trying to comfort or quiet it, and the thing just kept writing and screaming the whole time we walked past. It didn't help that I was walking last through this part. It was pretty scary.
QID53: Trying to remember it wasn't real, and to prime/prepare myself for jump scares so they wouldn't be as bad. At least I'd be able to tell myself, "I was expecting that."
QID398: Focused on the people around me, made sure not to look at the actors.
QID428: This was the one thing I really couldn't avoid or get away from. Instead, we all vocalized how uncomfortable we were to each other, which helped dispel some of the discomfort.
QID458: I was being extra attentive and looking behind me all the time to make sure I didn't get surprised by anything. That tenseness and attentiveness actually helped, overall. But it was nerve-wracking and scary. In the last section, the girl in front of me did suggest that we all keep a hand on each other's backs so as to stay together and not be as frightened. It helped a little!
QID488: I know that the goal was to be scary, but I hate loud noises regardless. So I was frustrated by this feature, but there was nothing I could do about it. Instead, I just reminded myself that it would be over soon, and that everything was ok.

QID548: I did not try to change my attentiveness because I felt like it gave me more control (even though it really gave me none). QID578: This felt more like an exercise in discomfort. It was all pretty gruesome, but not that frightening.
QID608: We were able to talk in the lines, which really helped manage the fear.
QID638: I felt that it was pretty normal to be disgusted by this thing, so I didn't really try to change that. But I found I couldn't NOT pay attention to it. That was strange. QID3: The scariest part was this room that had hanging bodies in it. QID3: So I did not put this event first, but BREAK OUT was first. The people were in all of the jail cells. They were trying to break out obviously. I remember thinking the cell bars were super far apart of course it would be easy to break out. It also reminded me of Shawshank Redemption. People were dirty, but also wearing white.
QID6: This one I am not sure what it was called, but it had "soldiers" and "ninjas". It was a lot of yelling about getting down and not hitting their lasers. I was still scared, but it was a lot of flickering lights and fake smoke.
QID7: Machine yard I believe was next. The people were majority black men and some white men with shaved heads. It was kind of your stereotypical "jail job", the inmates had chainsaws and there were chains all around. All the men in this part were very big men. The most memorable part of this was the women on a bungee cord apparatus and how she almost kicked one of the people in our group.
QID8: Infirmary. The girl who was letting everyone in looked like a dirty experimented on patient, but her makeup was poppin. She killed it. We walk in and it's a long hallway and there are little door frames that people kept popping out of. At the end of the hall there was a "doctor" performing open stomach surgery on a patient. Following that we walked there the fake hospital with many nurses and doctors trying to scare us. I remember thinking, "Why didn't someone pop out of the bed, because that actually would've scared me more". Following that we left and it wasn't super memorable.
QID10: This was the freak show, neon light, 3D portion of the haunted house. Not scary at all in my opinion, because it was very well lit. This one had potential to be scarier with better places actors to jump out, because of the 3D glasses. There were clowns, spiders, people "blending" in with the walls, very American Horror Story Freak Shows, but with neon colors. Not too scary, more so entertaining and trippy. I was only nervous at this moment, because I was leading the group. We walked out and moved on to the next part and that's when the computer turned off that was helping monitor our heart rates.

QID3: Once we signed TBtW's consents, the other participants and I continued to walk. Then we heard the two lab managers call at us and we saw that they were at a corner waiting for us, so we turned around and met up with them. While there, they had us turn on our recorders and explained that we would be rating how scary the houses were on a scale of 1-5.
QID6: The recorders were labeled numerically. The person with the recorder labeled "1" was the person to lead us the way in the first house. The person with the "1" recorder was the other female participant.
QID7: Throughout the entire first house, I remember walking through laughing because that's apparently my response to fear. At a few points, I remember holding onto the other female participant's bag because it was dark and I kept getting scared.
QID8: After the second house, one of the lab managers let us know that she was unable to complete the rest of the houses because she was just recovering from a concussion and realized that she wasn't ready to go back in just yet. She left the group at this point.
QID10: I think after this, we were in the Contagion house. One of the actors gave a balloon with an "X" to the male participant and told him that if he lets go of it or pops it, there is a disease in there that will I think kill everyone?
QID9: By the third house, I was not as scared. At this point, my ratings went from a 5/5 to a 3/5. The actors were still popping out and scaring us, but it seems like after the second house, the frequency decreased.
QID11: The fourth house was the house where I had to go in first. I was a little bit stressed out about that because that meant I wouldn't be able to hold on to anyone's bag if I got scared. However, I flew through it and I think I rated it a 3/5 or 2/5.
QID12: During the 5th house, one of the lab manager's went in first and I was directly behind her. The other participants were behind us and I could hear them screaming. The lab manager was ruthless, she barely flinched. I kept laughing.
QID14: I think in the last house, the actors gave us 3D glasses and I was not a fan. I took them off halfway.
QID15: We finished the haunted house and met up with the other lab manager who had to leave earlier. We made our final ratings.
